the children?

70
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:19,492
Their whole life.
I've known their parents-

71
00:08:19,699 --> 00:08:23,226
I knew their parents
since high schooI.

72
00:08:24,604 --> 00:08:27,903
Oh, that must be a terrible loss
for you too, then. Thanks, CaroI.

73
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:30,068
Yeah.

74
00:08:30,409 --> 00:08:33,674
Losing your friends beats what I'm
feeling right now, I'll tell you that.

75
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:36,212
Well, you're doing the right thing.

76
00:08:36,849 --> 00:08:40,080
- Am I?
- Yeah. Sign on the second page.

77
00:08:53,599 --> 00:08:54,964
Thanks.

78
00:09:43,382 --> 00:09:44,576
Excuse me...

79
00:09:46,185 --> 00:09:48,119
...can you keep a secret?

80
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:50,617
- What?
- A secret.

81
00:09:54,226 --> 00:09:56,854
- Yeah.
- Okay.

82
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:02,429
- Here.
- Thank you.

83
00:10:02,802 --> 00:10:04,667
You're welcome.

84
00:10:06,205 --> 00:10:09,368
Are you, like, the hall monitor
or something?

85
00:10:10,343 --> 00:10:11,640
No, I'm a mother.

86
00:10:14,213 --> 00:10:19,207
And my secret is that I know
that everyone in this place...

87
00:10:19,418 --> 00:10:21,181
...is just as scared as you are.

88
00:10:23,489 --> 00:10:26,515
And I know that because
I've been on both sides.

89
00:10:27,526 --> 00:10:28,993
Really?

90
00:10:30,329 --> 00:10:32,194
But you know what?

91
00:10:32,765 --> 00:10:34,858
I learned a lot about families.

92
00:10:35,067 --> 00:10:37,592
And I learned you have to
protect your children.

93
00:10:38,437 --> 00:10:40,928
And that you have to be
a good mother.

94
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,209
- Can we get we get some ice cream?
- Sure we can, buddy.

95
00:10:44,777 --> 00:10:49,510
Hi. I'm Raymond.
You must be Ethan's sister.

96
00:10:49,715 --> 00:10:52,445
- Yeah. Abby.
- Hi.

97
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:56,052
Are-? Are you taking him?

98
00:10:57,957 --> 00:11:00,391
We lost our boy.

99
00:11:03,596 --> 00:11:06,759
The truth is, I'm just not ready
to stop being a mother.

100
00:11:08,734 --> 00:11:09,962
He's really lucky.

101
00:11:15,775 --> 00:11:19,006
Now, be a big boy, Ethan.
And be really good, okay?

102
00:11:19,211 --> 00:11:21,179
Everything's gonna be okay.

103
00:11:25,384 --> 00:11:29,548
Don't worry. We're still gonna
see each other. All the time, okay?

104
00:11:32,792 --> 00:11:35,852
You know another thing
that I learned about families:

105
00:11:39,065 --> 00:11:41,090
It's that when you have
a five-bedroom home...

106
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:43,825
...you should definitely have
more than one child.

107
00:13:02,381 --> 00:13:04,076
Here we are.

108
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:07,309
This is the foyer.

109
00:13:08,154 --> 00:13:10,145
This is the formaI living room.

110
00:13:11,323 --> 00:13:12,984
Come on, Abby.

111
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:17,762
See this? This is an atrium.
Raymond designed that.

112
00:13:23,602 --> 00:13:25,331
No, Ethan, don't touch!

113
00:13:25,538 --> 00:13:29,269
It's all right. It's all right.
This is your home too.

114
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:32,239
Come on. This is the staircase.
It goes up to the bedrooms.

115
00:13:32,444 --> 00:13:35,538
I'll show you that in a minute.
This is the dining room.

116
00:13:36,715 --> 00:13:38,706
And this is the den.

117
00:13:39,418 --> 00:13:41,386
Raymond, wanna show him
what you bought him?

118
00:13:41,587 --> 00:13:45,785
Oh, yeah. Ethan, buddy.
Look straight ahead.

119
00:13:45,991 --> 00:13:48,824
- Yes!
- We'll never see him again.

120
00:13:49,895 --> 00:13:52,989
- I love this game.
- Okay, here we go.

121
00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:02,863
Now, up here we have
the bedrooms.

122
00:14:03,075 --> 00:14:07,603
This is our room. I expect
breakfast in bed every Mother's Day.

123
00:14:09,815 --> 00:14:12,750
Now, this- I think we can make this
a playroom. What do you think?

124
00:14:12,952 --> 00:14:15,750
- Yeah.
- Yeah? Okay.

125
00:14:15,955 --> 00:14:20,688
- Ethan, this is your room.
- Oh, this is so cooI.

126
00:14:22,561 --> 00:14:25,655
- You like it?
- I think he likes it.

127
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:29,489
Now, I unpacked your things.
I put them where they should be, okay.

128
00:14:29,969 --> 00:14:31,459
- Bathroom's right there.
- Okay.

129
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:33,228
All right.

130
00:14:33,672 --> 00:14:35,902
We put Ethan close to us.

131
00:14:36,108 --> 00:14:40,204
Why don't I show Abby the tower?
Your room. Come on.

132
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,344
You're gonna love it.

133
00:14:45,084 --> 00:14:47,518
Word of warning:
Eve is a light sleeper.

134
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:51,486
- No backflips or cartwheels, okay?
- Right.

135
00:14:51,690 --> 00:14:53,487
Here we are.

136
00:14:59,265 --> 00:15:01,290
I'm up here alone?

137
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:04,560
You're an adult now. Time for you
to have your own space.

138
00:15:07,439 --> 00:15:09,100
- You like it?
- Yeah.

139
00:15:09,308 --> 00:15:11,367
You have the best view
in the whole house.

140
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:15,274
Look out this window. You and Ethan
are gonna be so happy here.

141
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:29,957
- What's in there?
- Don't go in there.

142
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:34,324
That's was our son's room.
Do not go in there.

143
00:15:34,934 --> 00:15:36,629
Of course not.

144
00:15:39,071 --> 00:15:41,869
There he is. Why don't you two
get your rooms in order...

145
00:15:42,074 --> 00:15:44,736
...and I will meet you downstairs.
We'll eat in an hour.

146
00:15:44,944 --> 00:15:46,241
Okay.

147
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:50,112
I saw a lake when we drove up.

148
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,343
Come.

149
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:28,877
Be carefuI.

150
