Excuse me, Abby.
That's my father's gun.

200
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:29,652
His keepsake from the war.

201
00:21:29,855 --> 00:21:32,085
Eve thinks I got rid of it, so:

202
00:21:33,191 --> 00:21:35,989
All right, Ethan. You open it up, right?
Okay? See this?

203
00:21:36,194 --> 00:21:38,287
And then what you wanna do
is you set the dials.

204
00:21:38,497 --> 00:21:40,021
- Press?
- Okay. Yes.

205
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:42,757
Well, no, actually this one.
See, that one.

206
00:21:44,436 --> 00:21:47,405
That's what you're gonna have to
ask your sister. Abby?

207
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:50,602
I'd like to say this only once.

208
00:21:52,044 --> 00:21:56,140
Great. Okay. So then you have to
get detergent, which is up here.

209
00:21:56,381 --> 00:21:59,145
All right. Down the stairs
all the way to the top...

210
00:21:59,351 --> 00:22:01,376
...through that door is the attic.

211
00:22:02,187 --> 00:22:04,348
A lot of work to do.

212
00:22:17,402 --> 00:22:18,960
After you.

213
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:30,345
So, what do you think,
is it hot in here?

214
00:22:31,416 --> 00:22:32,644
No.

215
00:22:33,819 --> 00:22:35,446
- Not really.
- Well, this should be...

216
00:22:35,654 --> 00:22:38,088
...the hottest room in the house.
Especially in summer.

217
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:40,850
That means all the hot air
is escaping.

218
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:44,218
- Isn't that a good thing?
- Well, no. Not in the winter.

219
00:22:44,429 --> 00:22:47,762
I boarded this with new insulation
and you can help me with the rest.

220
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:51,330
Okay? Lose this window,
we'll make it airtight.

221
00:22:51,536 --> 00:22:53,731
What do you think?
We'll do a little each day.

222
00:22:53,939 --> 00:22:56,066
Be a nice way for us to
get to know each other.

223
00:22:56,274 --> 00:22:57,571
- Okay.
- Good. Tell you what.

224
00:22:57,776 --> 00:23:01,007
You... You can wear my tooI belt.

225
00:23:03,815 --> 00:23:06,545
Leave it. It's okay.
I got plenty of those.

226
00:23:06,752 --> 00:23:08,686
- Okay.
- Can you handle it?

227
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:11,281
Good.

228
00:23:30,642 --> 00:23:31,973
<i>David.</i>

229
00:24:33,538 --> 00:24:35,938
Why are you here?
You are never to come in here.

230
00:24:36,141 --> 00:24:38,132
You promised, Abby.

231
00:24:38,710 --> 00:24:40,541
Sorry.

232
00:24:43,882 --> 00:24:45,873
Can you keep a secret?

233
00:24:46,685 --> 00:24:48,710
- Yes.
- You sure?

234
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:50,182
Yeah.

235
00:24:50,689 --> 00:24:52,520
Don't tell Eve.

236
00:24:53,525 --> 00:24:55,254
Really, don't.

237
00:24:56,828 --> 00:24:59,296
- Okay.
- Good.

238
00:24:59,498 --> 00:25:02,365
Come on, now get out of here
before Eve finds you.

239
00:25:29,728 --> 00:25:31,753
Abby, where are you going?

240
00:25:34,566 --> 00:25:36,090
Walk.

241
00:25:36,301 --> 00:25:37,996
It's lunchtime.

242
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:40,763
Oh, no, it's fine. I'll have
mine when I get back.

243
00:25:41,139 --> 00:25:42,902
I don't want you wandering outside.

244
00:25:43,108 --> 00:25:44,939
I'm not wandering,
I'm going to the lake.

245
00:25:45,610 --> 00:25:48,135
No. Absolutely not.

246
00:25:48,346 --> 00:25:50,211
Why not?

247
00:25:51,149 --> 00:25:53,913
Because this is my house,
and these are my rules...

248
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:57,247
...and it's for your own good.
Do I have to spell it out?

249
00:25:57,455 --> 00:26:00,117
- What is the problem?
- How about no lunch...

250
00:26:00,325 --> 00:26:03,089
...and no walk.
Now go to your room!

251
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:07,296
Okay.

252
00:26:11,202 --> 00:26:12,635
Sorry.

253
00:27:02,387 --> 00:27:04,446
Abby, can you get the door please?

254
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:12,428
There's no one at the door.
There's never anyone at the door.

