00:27:26,211 --> 00:27:29,510
- Hey.
- Oh, my God, hi!

256
00:27:29,714 --> 00:27:31,181
<i>How are you?</i>

257
00:27:32,784 --> 00:27:33,978
<i>Hey, buddy.</i>

258
00:27:34,185 --> 00:27:35,812
Hey.

259
00:27:40,492 --> 00:27:43,017
<i>Eve was right.
You two are stir-crazy.</i>

260
00:27:43,228 --> 00:27:45,219
She should know.

261
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:51,560
Well, it's a nice big house.

262
00:27:52,470 --> 00:27:53,869
<i>Great view.</i>

263
00:27:54,072 --> 00:27:55,733
There's a game room
with a PlayStation.

264
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:59,000
See, it doesn't get any
better than that, does it?

265
00:28:00,745 --> 00:28:02,144
Hey.

266
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:06,013
What's going on with you?

267
00:28:06,885 --> 00:28:08,079
Get us out of here.

268
00:28:08,853 --> 00:28:12,118
<i>She is so weird.
It's like they have all this land...</i>

269
00:28:12,323 --> 00:28:15,724
...and we're not allowed to leave
the house. There's a gross mattress...

270
00:28:15,927 --> 00:28:17,758
...in the basement.
We can't use the phone.

271
00:28:17,962 --> 00:28:19,930
<i>We need a dial-out code
to make a phone call.</i>

272
00:28:20,131 --> 00:28:24,534
Abby. Look, you gotta
try to make this work.

273
00:28:24,736 --> 00:28:27,603
I don't know if
Eve or Raymond told you this...

274
00:28:27,806 --> 00:28:31,139
...but you know they lost their
little boy, their son, David, right?

275
00:28:31,342 --> 00:28:34,834
- Yeah.
- He drowned. Down at the lake.

276
00:28:36,448 --> 00:28:38,609
I tell you because
if you think they're mean...

277
00:28:38,817 --> 00:28:41,877
...or if they don't
understand, believe me...

278
00:28:42,087 --> 00:28:44,021
...they do understand.

279
00:28:46,357 --> 00:28:48,825
Make it work for a few more weeks.

280
00:28:49,360 --> 00:28:52,022
Because then, when I come back
to take you to Six Flags...

281
00:28:52,230 --> 00:28:54,027
- Six Flags!
- ... I wanna see smiles...

282
00:28:54,232 --> 00:28:55,961
...on both of your faces.

283
00:28:56,568 --> 00:28:58,035
Hey.

284
00:29:35,673 --> 00:29:38,301
Why is there a mattress
in the basement?

285
00:29:40,311 --> 00:29:42,336
Why are you sneaking around
in the basement?

286
00:29:42,547 --> 00:29:44,811
I'm not sneaking, it's just,
there's nowhere to go.

287
00:29:45,016 --> 00:29:47,075
You guys don't even let us
out of the house.

288
00:29:48,586 --> 00:29:50,520
Don't be silly,
we let you out of the house.

289
00:29:50,722 --> 00:29:53,919
No, you don't.
You're always watching.

290
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:56,855
Well, is there something
you don't want us to see?

291
00:29:57,061 --> 00:29:58,551
No.

292
00:29:58,763 --> 00:30:01,755
We are responsible for you.
We protect you.

293
00:30:03,434 --> 00:30:05,334
Ben protects us.

294
00:30:05,570 --> 00:30:07,037
Ben Koch?

295
00:30:07,238 --> 00:30:09,468
The man who lives downtown
in a one-bedroom apartment?

296
00:30:09,674 --> 00:30:11,733
- That's who protects you?
- Yes.

297
00:30:11,943 --> 00:30:13,342
He said we can stay with him.

298
00:30:13,845 --> 00:30:17,713
- Ben doesn't want to be your parent.
- You don't know that.

299
00:30:18,483 --> 00:30:21,452
Where is this attitude
coming from, young lady?

300
00:30:21,653 --> 00:30:23,951
This is all for you.

301
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:26,885
For your safety. Your own parents
couldn't protect you.

302
00:30:28,593 --> 00:30:33,553
Don't you dare talk about my parents.
You don't know my parents.

303
00:30:33,765 --> 00:30:35,824
We are your parents.

304
00:30:36,034 --> 00:30:37,831
Fuck you.

305
00:30:44,442 --> 00:30:48,640
I wouldn't do that if I were you.

306
00:30:48,847 --> 00:30:51,077
Now sit down!

307
00:31:01,893 --> 00:31:04,259
- Honey, I think that-
- Raymond, don't.

308
00:31:12,604 --> 00:31:15,095
It's okay, Ethan.
Eat your food.

309
00:31:15,306 --> 00:31:17,035
It's okay.

310
00:31:31,623 --> 00:31:35,889
House is locked tight.
Rug rats are asleep.

311
00:31:38,396 --> 00:31:40,523
No, it's not right.

312
00:31:40,965 --> 00:31:42,626
Not yet.

313
00:32:26,744 --> 00:32:28,678
Hi, honey.

314
00:32:30,581 --> 00:32:32,549
Raymond, are you gonna clean up?

315
00:32:32,750 --> 00:32:35,275
- Why?
- She's gonna be here at 3:00.

316
00:32:36,554 --> 00:32:39,079
Yes. I'll be ready.

317
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:41,815
- Morning, Abby.
- Hi.

318
00:32:45,063 --> 00:32:46,758
Who's gonna be here at 3:00?

319
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:48,762
Caseworker.

320
00:32:50,034 --> 00:32:52,264
And you missed breakfast.

321
00:32:54,305 --> 00:32:56,535
It's 8:30.

322
00:33:09,654 --> 00:33:11,053
You know, Abby...

323
00:33:11,255 --> 00:33:13,815
...you might wanna
clean up a bit for the caseworker.

324
00:33:14,025 --> 00:33:18,485
Put your hair back.
Put a cute sweater on. Like mine.

325
00:33:19,330 --> 00:33:22,322
It's just nice to make an effort
when guests are coming, you know?

326
00:33:22,533 --> 00:33:23,727
No offense.

327
00:33:24,902 --> 00:33:28,167
<i>Actually, I'm not really into that
whole Stepford Wives look.</i>

328
00:33:29,273 --> 00:33:30,865
No offense.

329
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:04,670
What's with the lockdown?
Are we under siege?

330
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:08,334
Around here we protect
our family, Abby.

331
00:34:11,315 --> 00:34:12,942
You look cute.

332
00:34:27,432 --> 00:34:29,332
What was wrong
with the other alarm?

333
00:34:29,534 --> 00:34:33,368
Your mom bought an upgrade.
Double locks on all the doors.

334
00:34:34,205 --> 00:34:35,900
She's not my mom.

335
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:41,045
- Hi.
- Hey.

336
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:44,011
May I speak to you
for a moment, please?

337
00:34:54,425 --> 00:34:56,188
Right here is fine.

338
00:34:57,462 --> 00:34:59,657
I don't know what outhouse
you were raised in...

339
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:03,099
...but don't ever say a nasty
remark about me again.

340
00:35:03,301 --> 00:35:05,599
Otherwise, you're out of here.

341
00:35:06,104 --> 00:35:08,368
And Ethan stays with us.

342
00:35:13,811 --> 00:35:15,972
You're in my way, Eve.

343
00:35:16,180 --> 00:35:19,445
I'm twice the bitch
you think you are.

344
00:35:32,997 --> 00:35:35,761
It's just a standard checklist.
It shouldn't take too long.

345
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:38,800
But I do ask that you let
the children show me around.

346
00:35:39,003 --> 00:35:40,630
Of course.

347
00:35:41,506 --> 00:35:44,202
Okay, Abby and Ethan,
show me your rooms.

348
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:49,670
So, Ethan, you like your new home?

349
00:35:49,881 --> 00:35:52,850
- Yeah.
- Yeah? All right.

350
00:36:13,337 --> 00:36:14,668
Nice.

351
00:36:18,543 --> 00:36:19,976
Lonely up here?

352
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:25,338
Anything you want
to talk to me about?

353
00:36:28,419 --> 00:36:30,546
If we stay with this couple...

354
00:36:30,755 --> 00:36:33,656
...and I leave to go to college...

355
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:35,587
...what happens to my brother?

356
00:36:35,793 --> 00:36:39,354
Well, he could stay right here in
foster care and they could adopt him.

357
00:36:39,564 --> 00:36:42,624
Adopt him?
What if I wanted to adopt him?

358
00:36:42,833 --> 00:36:46,030
What if I wanted him to stay with me?
I have no say in that whatsoever?

359
00:36:46,237 --> 00:36:49,297
You can be his legaI guardian
by the time you're 18.

360
00:36:50,641 --> 00:36:53,576
And when I do turn 18...

361
00:36:55,246 --> 00:36:56,907
...they can't do anything to stop me?

362
00:36:59,050 --> 00:37:02,451
You have a claim to your little brother
for as long as you live.

363
00:37:03,521 --> 00:37:05,921
And no one can take that
away from you.

364
00:37:06,824 --> 00:37:08,382
Okay?

365
00:37:12,029 --> 00:37:13,997
It's okay.

366
00:37:19,537 --> 00:37:21,630
Any other sedatives?

367
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,434
No.

368
00:37:23,641 --> 00:37:27,543
- Any codeine? Any Vicodin?
- No.

369
00:37:27,745 --> 00:37:31,545
Don't most adults have some sort
of pain medication?

370
00:37:31,749 --> 00:37:33,182
But you know children.

371
00:37:33,384 --> 00:37:37,184
They explore. They're curious and we
don't want their curiosity to kill them.

372
00:37:37,388 --> 00:37:41,688
So just be carefuI with what kind of
medication you have in the home.

373
00:37:42,326 --> 00:37:43,486
Of course.

374
00:37:48,466 --> 00:37:49,660
Okay. Take care, now.

375
00:37:49,867 --> 00:37:51,698
- It was our pleasure.
- Thanks for coming.

376
00:37:51,902 --> 00:37:54,496
- Have a safe trip back to the city.
- All right. Bye.

377
00:37:54,705 --> 00:37:56,696
Let me get that.

378
00:37:58,042 --> 00:38:02,035
Aren't you gonna
check the basement?

379
00:38:04,782 --> 00:38:07,114
Well, should I check the basement?

380
00:38:09,820 --> 00:38:11,651
David would play alone down here.

381
00:38:11,856 --> 00:38:14,416
We've learned to keep
a better eye on our kids.

382
00:38:14,892 --> 00:38:18,225
It was right here.
There used to be a bed right here.

383
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:20,294
- He slept here. There used to-
- Honestly.

384
00:38:20,498 --> 00:38:22,932
- You think there was a bed here?
- Why do you think that?

385
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:25,728
I don't know,
I just know it was right here.

386
00:38:26,637 --> 00:38:28,696
Well, there were some old blankets.

387
00:38:28,906 --> 00:38:30,965
I threw them away.

388
00:38:32,043 --> 00:38:33,510
What has gotten into you?

389
00:38:33,711 --> 00:38:35,611
You know,
she said this to us last night.

390
00:38:35,813 --> 00:38:37,303
Just...

391
00:38:37,515 --> 00:38:39,540
Is this about
our conversation upstairs?

392
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:42,617
- No.
- About your brother?

393
00:38:42,853 --> 00:38:46,846
No! No, that's not it at all.
There was a bed right here.

394
00:38:47,058 --> 00:38:49,288
Okay, enough. Let's go upstairs.

395
00:38:49,493 --> 00:38:50,824
I'm so sorry.

396
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:57,357
Abby, come on.

397
00:38:58,703 --> 00:39:00,330
Come on.

398
00:39:02,540 --> 00:39:05,168
- Drive safe. Bye.
- Okay. Bye-bye.

399
00:41:53,978 --> 00:41:56,003
I made your favorite.

400
00:42:02,353 --> 00:42:03,752
What about the kids' dinner?

401
00:42:06,490 --> 00:42:08,390
Isn't this perfect?

402
00:42:18,269 --> 00:42:19,702
Eve?

403
00:42:20,905 --> 00:42:22,338
Honey?

404
00:42:24,174 --> 00:42:25,732
Honey, talk to me.

405
00:42:33,384 --> 00:42:35,875
It'll be different this time, I promise.

406
00:42:40,024 --> 00:42:41,491
Chicken.

407
00:42:41,692 --> 00:42:44,252
Peas. Salad.

408
00:42:44,929 --> 00:42:46,328
Wine.

409
00:42:48,399 --> 00:42:50,026
Perfect.

410
00:42:55,339 --> 00:42:57,239
Drink your wine, Raymond.

411
00:44:53,424 --> 00:44:55,016
Sit up.

412
00:45:12,409 --> 00:45:14,536
You have chores.

413
00:45:14,745 --> 00:45:17,646
Afterwards, maybe you can go
with your mother to run some errands.

414
00:45:17,848 --> 00:45:19,577
Get you out of the house.

415
00:45:22,586 --> 00:45:24,247
Raymond.

416
00:45:27,357 --> 00:45:29,052
I'm sorry.

417
00:45:31,195 --> 00:45:32,685
No worries.

418
00:45:32,896 --> 00:45:34,727
I'll be in the office.

419
00:45:49,046 --> 00:45:50,741
Hi there.

420
00:45:51,482 --> 00:45:52,847
Raymond said I have chores.

421
00:45:53,083 --> 00:45:54,414
Sit down.

422
00:45:54,618 --> 00:45:56,882
Relax. Take it easy.

423
00:45:58,021 --> 00:46:02,082
Oh, would you mind finishing
the dishes I left in the sink?

424
00:46:02,526 --> 00:46:05,324
- Okay.
- Great. Thank you.

425
00:46:34,625 --> 00:46:36,786
- What'd you do?
- I don't know!

426
00:46:36,994 --> 00:46:38,928
- Cut myself!
- Eve, Abby hurt herself.

427
00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:41,654
Oh, God. It hurts really bad.

428
00:46:41,865 --> 00:46:43,423
Oh, my God!

429
00:46:43,634 --> 00:46:45,192
Don't move.

430
00:46:56,146 --> 00:46:57,738
I want to go to the hospitaI.

431
00:46:57,948 --> 00:47:00,314
Eve was a nurse, Abby.

432
00:47:00,517 --> 00:47:02,576
Oh, dear. Look at that.

433
00:47:03,020 --> 00:47:04,954
It's okay, it's okay.

434
00:47:05,756 --> 00:47:07,917
Can't be clumsy
when dealing with glass, Abby.

435
00:47:08,125 --> 00:47:10,650
It was already broken, Eve.

436
00:47:12,896 --> 00:47:14,090
What are you doing?

437
00:47:16,133 --> 00:47:17,395
- Be still.
- I don't want that.

438
00:47:17,601 --> 00:47:19,466
- It's okay.
- I really don't want it.

439
00:47:19,670 --> 00:47:21,797
It's okay, Abby.

440
00:47:25,909 --> 00:47:27,809
Now, you ever had stitches?

441
00:47:28,946 --> 00:47:30,607
Hold still.

442
00:47:35,686 --> 00:47:37,620
Oh, my God!

443
00:47:37,855 --> 00:47:39,220
Raymond, hold her.

444
00:47:39,756 --> 00:47:40,984
Oh, my God!

445
00:47:44,328 --> 00:47:46,159
- This is what a mother does, Abby.
- My God!

446
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:51,898
She comforts her child.

447
00:47:52,769 --> 00:47:54,964
Heals her when she's sick.

448
00:47:56,807 --> 00:47:59,469
Corrects her when she's wrong.

449
00:48:02,412 --> 00:48:04,073
Oh, my God.

450
00:48:04,281 --> 00:48:05,908
She does it because she wants to.

451
00:48:09,920 --> 00:48:11,410
Expecting nothing in return.

452
00:48:12,923 --> 00:48:15,391
Oh, my God.

453
00:48:16,093 --> 00:48:18,527
That's all I've ever wanted to be.

454
00:48:18,729 --> 00:48:20,128
Oh, my God!

455
00:48:20,330 --> 00:48:22,491
To be a good mother.

456
00:48:32,709 --> 00:48:35,007
- What is that?
- This is for pain.

457
00:48:38,081 --> 00:48:40,879
- I'm not in pain.
- You will be.

458
00:49:50,053 --> 00:49:52,487
- But he promised.
- Your father is very busy.

459
00:49:52,689 --> 00:49:54,782
He doesn't have time
to drive you to a cemetery.

460
00:49:54,992 --> 00:49:57,153
- He's not my father.
- Ethan.

461
00:49:57,361 --> 00:49:58,828
He's not.

462
00:49:59,029 --> 00:50:00,690
Don't, Ethan.

463
00:50:01,732 --> 00:50:03,529
What are you doing
out of bed, Abby?

464
00:50:04,735 --> 00:50:07,499
I don't feeI well.
What did you give me?

465
00:50:09,139 --> 00:50:10,333
I can make you some eggs.

466
00:50:10,540 --> 00:50:11,734
No.

467
00:50:11,942 --> 00:50:13,307
Toast?

468
00:50:13,510 --> 00:50:14,909
No.

469
00:50:15,379 --> 00:50:17,142
You have to eat something.

470
00:50:20,584 --> 00:50:24,179
Ben Koch called yesterday.
I told him about your condition.

471
00:50:24,821 --> 00:50:26,550
Yesterday I was fine.

472
00:50:27,424 --> 00:50:30,222
No, Abby, you've been
in bed for three days.

473
00:50:34,965 --> 00:50:37,331
He said he'd stop by when he could.

474
00:50:48,945 --> 00:50:50,810
Eat up, baby.

475
00:51:29,486 --> 00:51:31,078
- Oh, my God, Ethan.
- Help me.

476
00:51:31,288 --> 00:51:32,949
- Are you okay?
- I'm reaI sick.

477
00:51:33,156 --> 00:51:35,954
- Oh, my God.
- Okay, doctor, thank you.

478
00:51:36,159 --> 00:51:39,617
Yes, fluids. All right,
thank you very much.

479
00:51:41,631 --> 00:51:43,826
So he said to just keep doing
what we're doing.

480
00:51:44,034 --> 00:51:45,592
That dehydration is the danger.

481
00:51:45,802 --> 00:51:47,565
Was it food poisoning?

482
00:51:47,771 --> 00:51:50,740
I don't know, honey.
I mean, we all ate the same thing.

483
00:51:53,443 --> 00:51:56,435
- I wanna use the phone.
- Why?

484
00:51:56,646 --> 00:51:58,637
I wanna call Ben
and tell him about this.

485
00:52:00,484 --> 00:52:03,146
- All right, I'll call him tomorrow.
- Why can't I call him?

486
00:52:03,720 --> 00:52:06,188
Because it's 3:00
in the morning, Abby.

487
00:52:06,389 --> 00:52:08,380
Eve will take care of it.

488
00:52:10,160 --> 00:52:12,890
And I want you in your
own bed tonight, all right?

489
00:52:16,766 --> 00:52:19,257
It's all right, baby, Mommy's here.

490
00:52:19,469 --> 00:52:21,232
It's okay, Ethan.

491
00:52:21,438 --> 00:52:22,632
I'm here.

492
00:53:55,265 --> 00:53:57,358
You're not having any dinner, Abby?

493
00:54:02,005 --> 00:54:04,371
Have some soup, sweetie.

494
00:54:27,197 --> 00:54:29,563
I made it for Ethan.

495
00:56:11,768 --> 00:56:14,236
Good morning, Ethan.

496
00:56:16,005 --> 00:56:19,964
Lots of fluids. Doctor's orders.

497
00:56:22,512 --> 00:56:24,878
This is warm tea.

498
00:56:26,716 --> 00:56:28,911
It's easy on your tummy,
make you feeI better.

499
00:56:34,023 --> 00:56:35,581
This is not food poisoning.

500
00:56:36,860 --> 00:56:38,418
It's not?

501
00:56:38,628 --> 00:56:41,153
No. It's obviously
something else.

502
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:44,033
Take him to the hospitaI.

503
00:56:45,301 --> 00:56:47,030
I can do it all here.

504
00:56:48,805 --> 00:56:50,329
You said you were gonna call Ben.

505
00:56:56,212 --> 00:56:58,772
I called Ben.
He's gonna come by later this week.

506
00:57:00,683 --> 00:57:01,877
When did you talk to him?

507
00:57:06,222 --> 00:57:08,247
About an hour ago.
While you were sleeping.

508
00:57:09,559 --> 00:57:10,890
Well, call him again.

509
00:57:11,861 --> 00:57:15,558
Mind your manners, Abby. The man
isn't at your beck and call, all right.

510
00:57:20,670 --> 00:57:22,501
